================================================================================
TROUBLESHOOTING
================================================================================

"ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'openpyxl'"
  Run: pip install openpyxl numpy

"FNO_Top10_Picks.xlsx not found"
  Run fno_top10_picker.py first before running the contract selector.

"No option chain CSV found for TICKER"
  Check the CSV is in the same folder as the script.
  Accepted filenames:
    TICKER_optionchain.csv
    option-chain-ED-TICKER-DD-Mon-YYYY.csv
  The ticker must match exactly (e.g. BHARATFORG not BharatForge).

"Could not find header row" error on Top 10 file
  The FNO_Top10_Picks.xlsx may be from an older version.
  Re-run fno_top10_picker.py to regenerate it fresh.

"positions.json" out of date after adding a new trade
  Run: python fno_position_tracker.py --add
  Follow the prompts to add the new position.

Script runs but shows wrong spot price
  The option chain CSV may be from a different date.
  Always download a fresh CSV on the day you run the selector.

